1998", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="Application of the conventional X.500 approach to naming has heretofore, in the experience of the authors, proven to be an obstacle to the wide deployment of directory-enabled applications on the Internet.  We propose a new directory naming plan that leverages the strengths of the most popular and successful Internet naming schemes for naming objects in a hierarchical directory.  This memo provides information for the Internet community.  It does not specify an Internet standard of any kind.", style=filled, fillcolor=green]; 

